<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5810] Include emma.jar on classpath when running compatibility test with instrumented jars</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5810</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running the compatibility test with EMMA instrumented jars, it fails because it starts sub-processes without putting emma.jar on their classpath. We should make it construct a working classpath for its sub-processes if it detects that it&apos;s running with instrumented jars.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will be easier to fix once &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5808&quot; title=&quot;Compatibility test should use BaseTestCase.execJavaCmd()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-5808&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-5808&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is checked in.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12560338">DERBY-5810</key>
            <summary>Include emma.jar on classpath when running compatibility test with instrumented jars</summary>
